  "commentary": "With SPX at 7022 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive +10.4B positive gamma wall at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging zone but approaching heavy selling pressure. The PIN regime confirms dealers will aggressively sell any push toward 7050 and provide buying support if we retest the 7015 negative gamma pocket, creating a tight 35-point trading range with strong mean reversion characteristics. Watch for dealer selling to intensify above 7030 as we approach the 7050 wall, while any dip toward 7015 should see immediate dealer buying support.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy action trapped between 7015-7050 with resistance building toward the upper end.",
